news.title: Telangana pays mere 0.1% of pending property tax owed to civic body
news.para: The RTI reply given to secretary of Forum for Good Governance (FGG) M Padmanabha Reddy reveals that 19 state government departments paid paltry sums between 2 lakh and 3 crore.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body agrees to review increase in property tax
news.para: A monthly general council meeting of the MCC held on Tuesday witnessed pandemonium when the Congress in the opposition did not accept the hike in property tax, which the urban local body implemented recently.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body issues 5,000 property attachment notices for tax
news.para: The Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) has recovered Rs645 crore this fiscal, the highest recovery recorded for the tax department.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body seals two buildings over default in property tax payment
news.para: As per MC officials, both these buildings fall under commercial category and the owners had failed to submit the property tax, which amounts to around Rs 3 lakh.

news.title: Aadhaar a must to sell or buy property in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: Registrations of sale deeds are being withheld at AP registrar's office without Aadhaar cards despite the Supreme Court ruling not to link it with essential services.

news.title: Vadodara civic body collects over Rs 2 crore towards pending rent
news.para: Several elected functionaries, including mayor and Sayajigunj MLA Keyur Rokadia and assembly chief whip Balkrishna Shukla, have been meeting shopkeepers in the complex for the last couple of months over various issues, including overdue rents.

news.title: Income tax searches at Googee Properties
news.para: The company has been involved in several real estate transactions on hundreds of acres in south Hyderabad, officials said.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to prevent sale deed registration of illegal property
news.para: On Thursday, Municipal Commissioner M Thennarasan shot off a circular to officials of all municipal zones - including estate officers -prescribing a standard operating procedure (SOP) of action to be taken against illegal structures in the city.

news.title: Reliance Industries enters commercial real estate business
news.para: "The company has incorporated a wholly owned subsidiary named Reliance SOU (RSOUL) to carry on, inter alia, the business of development of properties for commercial use," it said in a BSE filing.

news.title: LG approves draft Delhi master plan-2041
news.para: The Authority in its meeting, also took a decision for relaxation in guidelines pertaining to woman beneficiaries for in situ rehabilitation under the 'Jahan Jhuggi Wahan Makan' programme, the DDA said in a statement.

news.title: Housing finance companies to face headwinds amid rising interest rates: Report
news.para: For the top 12 HFCs, NPAs peaked at 2.9 per cent in FY21, and then marginally improved to 2.8 per cent in FY22. The overall stressed book (defaults and restructured loans) remained around 4 per cent in both FY22 and FY21.

news.title: Navi Mumbai builder Nalin Shah gets clean chit in cheating case
news.para: The Economic Offences Wing (EOW) of Navi Mumbai Crime branch had in July 2018 arrested Shah after the complainant Heena Shaikh (33), a Seawoods resident, had lodged a cheating complaint against him.

news.title: NGT asks if inquiry into green violation held in Mumbai SRA project
news.para: Last year, the NGT had passed an order restraining the builder, Skylark Buildcon and Oberoi Realty, from selling flats in the project’s free sale component till it provided 500 car parks for the slum rehabilitation buildings.

news.title: Nandan Nilekani's NRJN Family Trust sells Bengaluru residential asset for Rs 55 crore
news.para: The property, spread over 9,488 sq ft, is located at 3rd Cross, 3rd Block, Koramangala and was sold to V Seetha, the wife of C Valliappa, an industrialist and the founder of the Sona Valliappa Group (an extension of The Sona Group).

news.title: YEIDA cancels allotment of two plots to Supertech over Rs 86 crore dues
news.para: The developer, however, termed the move illegal citing the insolvency proceedings that were initiated against it in March 2022 for defaulting on payment of Rs 431 crore to a consortium of banks.
